<TEXT>
us and soviet diplomats opened talks sunday on 
southern africa and its racial conflicts in preparation for a new 
round of fournation negotiations aimed at bringing peace to the 
region 
cuban angolan south african and us delegations are to resume 
talks here tuesday on the future of angola and southwest africa a 
territory controlled by south africas whiteminority governmet 
that session is scheduled to last three days and is the fifth 
publicly announced round since negotiations were started in london 
last april 
chester crocker us assistant secretary of state for african 
affairs conferred with soviet deputy foreign minister anatoly 
adamishin for 3 hours sunday at the soviet mission no details 
were given of their their talks that are set to end monday 
the fournation conference will attempt to build on a set of 
principles initialed by cuba angola and south africa at a meeting 
july 13 in new york 
that accord commits the parties to seek a timetable for south 
africa to relinquish control over southwest africa also known as 
namibia under a un plan for the territory to gain its 
independence 
south africa has been battling guerrillas of the southwest 
african peoples organization for control of the territory for more 
than a decade south africa accuses angolas marxist governmment of 
harboring and supporing the guerrillas and has frequently sent its 
troops into southern angola 
south africa and the united states support anticommunist 
guerrillas of the national union for the total independence of 
angola unita who have been fighting the government since they 
were defeated in a civil war by the marxists after angola won 
independence from portugal in november 1975 
cuba is participating in the talks because it has more than 
40000 military personnel in angola helping the government fight 
the rebels 
south africa has said it would not grant independence to namibia 
until the cuban forces are withdrawn south africa has administered 
namibia a former german territory since the end of world war i 
under a mandate by the defunct league of nations the united 
nations repudiated that mandate and south africa rejected un 
resolutions calling for indpendence and free elections in the 
territory 
crocker on july 20 called the agreement on principles an 
important step but said there are a great many hard and difficult 
compromises to be achieved 
previous rounds in the talks included sessions in london cairo 
and new york and a meeting of top military officers from the four 
sides in the cape verde islands 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

