<TEXT>
gazing up at the sheer limestone 
north face of the eiger mountaineer heinrich harrer reminisced 
about the climb 50 years ago that changed his life 
in july 1938 he and three other climbers became the first to 
scale the daunting 5940foot wall in the heart of the swiss alps 
that is considered europes greatest challenge to mountaineers 
we were never afraid we never had any idea of returning or 
giving up despite difficulties during the fourday adventure the 
76yearold harrer told the associated press in a recent interview 
nine people had already died on the wall before harrer and fritz 
kasparek both austrians and andreas heckmair and ludwig voerg 
both germans set out before dawn one morning to conquer the last 
virgin face of the alps 
because of the danger authorities had outlawed attempts to 
climb the north face but the four defied the ban 
we climbed the wall secretly said harrer sitting in an 
alpine meadow with a dramatic view of the north face when we 
came down after four days we were surprised to find out that the 
whole world knew about it 
it turned out that observers had spotted them 
harrer recently returned to grindelwald a village at the base 
of the eiger for a weekend celebration with hundreds of other 
mountaineers and fans on the anniversary of the climb another 
guest of honor was 82yearold heckmair kasparek and voerg are 
both dead 
the eiger north face which juts up almost vertically above 
grindelwald lived up to its reputation that celebration weekend 
an english climber trying to scale it fell and sustained serious 
head injuries but was rescued alive by helicopter 
just saturday a 26yearold south korean was killed in a 
3300foot fall as he tried to scale the eigers north face the 
swiss air rescue service said 
the recent helicopter rescue recalled the most dramatic rescue 
from the eiger the first time a climber was rescued alive 
in 1957 before helicopters were used italian claudio corti was 
saved at an icy patch threequarters of the way up the wall but 
his countryman stefano longhi froze to death and his body hung from 
his rope out of reach of rescuers for two years 
it was only when winches were put in place in 1959 that the 
corpse could be retrieved 
harrer said that after 50 years public interest in the eiger 
and the historic first climb has actually increased 
this wall has developed a certain kind of charisma a mythical 
attraction he says 
since the 1938 climb about 700 mountaineers have successfully 
ascended the wall using various routes to get to the peak 13101 
feet above sea level 
harrer said the fact that so many have climbed the north face 
does not diminish the challenge 
fifty people have died on that wall which proves that the 
wall hasnt become easier he said 
but he added it has become easier provided you are an expert 
provided you are equipped properly provided you have prepared this 
climb and chosen the proper time to do it 
in a book he wrote about his ascent harrer tells how he and his 
partners waited for days watching the weather around the eiger 
before picking the best moment to begin their climb 
the climbers nourished themselves mostly with hot tea and cocoa 
harrer said his only solid food during the climb was a slice of 
bread and butter that his mother had given him 14 days earlier as 
he left home after taking his university exams 
i didnt tell her where i was going just that i was going 
climbing he said 
the most tense moments of the 1938 climb came on the third day 
when the mountaineers clung to the nearly vertical face to 
withstand avalanches hailstorms and snowstorms 
this is part of the eiger north wall harrer said 
he said he was not afraid once you start action you are on 
the wall you never think of any danger 
yet he said that before reaching the wall one always has some 
thoughts that you could return now it is not too late 
but its very simple if you dont overcome fear you will 
never be prepared to do something exceptional 
