vandals damaged the concrete tomb of 
president corazon aquinos husband but did not disturb the body a 
military official said today 
maj hernando patawaran spokesman for the presidential security 
group said the damage apparently was done late friday at the 
manila memorial park cemetery and was discovered saturday 
patawaran said the vandals pried loose a concrete slab from the 
top of the tomb of sen benigno aquino jr who was murdered aug 
21 1983 
patawaran said park authorities received a telephone call 
saturday saying a bomb had been planted in the tomb bomb experts 
inspected the site but found nothing he said 
soldiers guarded the tomb today and workers said they 
reinforced it with steel sheets 
a witness who visited the nearby grave of a relative saturday 
said presidential guards surrounded aquinos grave 
patawaran said officials did not know who vandalized the grave 
or why 
aquino was shot dead at manila international airport moments 
after he returned from three years of selfimposed exile in the 
united states 
the slaying fueled opposition to thenpresident ferdinand marcos 
that culminated in a militarycivilian uprising which toppled his 
administration in february 1986 and brought mrs aquino to power 
opposition leaders at the time blamed the marcos administration 
for the killing 
forty people most of them soldiers are on trial in the 
assassination 
