<TEXT>
thousands of holiday travelers 
rushing to board a ferry caused a pier to collapse leaving at 
least 31 people dead and injuring nearly 1000 officials and news 
reports said today 
survivors said the upper level of a twotiered pier in 
butterworth 180 miles northwest of kuala lumpur fell without 
warning sunday afternoon 
the upper section full of waiting passengers crashed onto people 
in cars and motorcycles on the lower level waiting to board the 
ferry 
victims were pinned beneath steel and timber while firefighters 
and port workers tried to free them and search for others 
emergency officials said all of those killed were believed to be 
malaysian 
about 300 people were on the pier and 3000 were lined up behind 
them when the rush to the ferry began port commission chairman 
syed mohhamad aidid told the national news agency bernama 
he said the 40foot section that collapsed normally held about 
200 people 
the travelers were waiting to make the threemile trip to penang 
island for the kwan yin goddess of mercy chinese religious 
celebration held once every 60 years 
everything happened so fast i could only scream for help 
gee swee cain 41 a supervisor of the passenger ferry at the pier 
told bernama 
as soon as the crowd rushed forward the piers wooden upper 
level gave way sending hundreds of people plummeting to the lower 
level said mrs gee who suffered chest and face injuries and a 
broken leg her husband and 5yearold child were uninjured 
i screamed for help and heard someone from above telling me to 
be patient because at that time nothing could be done to help me 
mrs gee told bernama 
cheong ah chey 21 who saw the pier collapse was quoted by the 
news agency as saying the crowd at the waiting area was moving 
toward the gate to get into the ferry which had just berthed when 
suddenly the platform below them gave way 
three cars entering the ferry were crushed and a port commission 
office was destroyed officials said 
the death toll from the collapse was considered likely to rise 
as many of the injured were hospitalized in critical condition 
bernama quoted police and other officials as saying 
hospitals and clinics in the area initially reported 969 people 
injured with 502 admitted and 467 treated and released bernama 
said officials today said 417 people remained hospitalized 
prime minister mahathir mohamad visited the injured at a 
government hospital he told reporters the government would give 
800 immediately to the family of each victim and that he would 
consider further compensation 
the port commission halted ferry service between butterworth and 
penang pending an inquiry traffic jammed penang bridge the only 
vehicle link to the island from the mainland after the closure of 
the ferry terminal 
despite the accident penang was crowded with thousands of 
people watching the festive parades in the streets 
the pier was built in 1956 and repaired from time to time 
bernama reported the platform that collapsed was last renovated in 
1986 when its planks and bolts were replaced 
the structure was built with pillars only at the sides of the 
structure and not in the center where the section failed 
