<TEXT>
an unusual crew left today to climb the 
north shoulder of mount everest through china and tibet a route so 
far conquered only by the chinese and spanish 
the group dubbed cowboys on everest contains five women 
including two who will attempt the final leg if sue cobb 50 and 
julie cheney 30 are successful they will become the first 
american women to climb the 29028 feet peak 
the climb was the idea of bob skinner 58 and his brother 
courtney 52 who operate a wilderness training school in pinedale 
wyo their friend george mccowen of menlo park raised nearly 1 
million for the climb which has become an official part of 
wyomings centennial celebration 
skinner told a news conference on sunday the 34member team 
includes mountaineers students artists doctors and geologists 
only six people will make the final summit assault 
