district of columbia superior court hearing commissioner kaye 
christian scheduled trial for sept 22 and released rowan on his 
own recognizance rowan requested a jury trial 
if he is convicted on both charges the columnist could face a 
maximum penalty of two years in prison and a 2000 fine 
the districts 1976 handgun ordinance essentially bans posession 
of handguns and ammunition not owned at the time the law was 
passed except for law officers 
