around a granite monument to polish officers murdered in the katyn 
forest near the soviet city of smolensk 
the massacre remains one of polands most bitter wartime 
memories and a sore spot in its relations with the soviet union 
the soviets have never acknowledged responsibility for the 
incident in which 4300 polish military officers were shot to 
death and left in a mass grave 
western historical sources indicate the poles were murdered on 
the orders of soviet dictator josef stalin in the spring of 1940 
