<TEXT>
the worlds anglican bishops on 
monday rejected a call to refrain from consecrating women bishops 
and accepted a compromise resolution that such elevation of women 
should not divide the anglican communion 
on a show of hands the bishops voted 42328 with 19 abstentions 
to maintain links with any of their 27 selfgoverning churches 
which consecrate a woman bishop even if they disagree 
the us episcopalians and the canadian and new zealand 
anglicans say they may consecrate a woman bishop by the end of this 
year 
the resolution preserving the unity of the 70 millionmember 
anglican communion was drafted by conference participants who 
considered it for most of the first two weeks of the threeweek 
lambeth conference 
it is the bishops first gathering in 10 years 
on a secret ballot the bishops voted 277187 against a 
resolution proposed by archbishop of sydney donald robinson that 
the churches should refrain from consecrating a woman as bishop 
to avoid further damage over the issue of women priests and bishops 
