ms jameson 
the fact is that if a marine in a position of high 
responsibility such as a drill instructor makes a statement under 
oath that shows he or she doesnt understand or support an order 
directly governing his or her duties it is within the discretion 
of the commander to consider removing that individual from that 
specific postion 
ms dibattiste said that although officers could be 
courtmartialed if found guilty of engaging in illegal command 
influence such charges are usually dropped 
all i can tell you is i think thats an appropriate allegation 
for defense council to make ms dibattiste said i would not 
render an opinion to you whether they would win or lose 
