<TEXT>
secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar 
said monday he will announce dday a date for a ceasefire in the 
8yearold iraniraq war after his factfinding team returns from 
those countries this week and he consults the security council 
the dday doesnt depend on the parties the un chief 
said indicating he could make a unilateral decision and go ahead 
without the agreement of iraq iran says it is ready to honor an 
immediate ceasefire 
perez de cuellar made the statement to reporters after a 
threehour meeting with iranian foreign minister ali akbar velayati 
announcement of a truce date would put pressure on iraq to 
compromise and drop its insistence on direct talks with iran before 
a ceasefire 
no immediate reaction surfaced from iraq 
perez de cuellar said a un military team of experts now is in 
amman jordan preparing its report and the team leader will 
present it to him in new york wednesday 
i will study his report i will be in touch with members of 
the security council and then i will decide on a dday perez 
de cuellar said 
it is very difficult to tell you now he said when asked if 
he would announce dday this week he cautioned against the idea 
that a ceasefire could be simply or rapidly implemented 
the secretarygeneral said once dday is decided he will begin 
consulting nations which could provide about 250 military observers 
to monitor the ceasefire and troop withdrawal 
the un chief held his sixth meeting with velayati since talks 
began last week he has met three times with iraqi foreign minister 
tariq aziz but iraq said it was not prepared to enter into 
substantive talks with perez de cuellar until direct talks take 
place 
iraqi officials also have not responded to a un report on 
chemical weapons which concluded that the baghdad government has 
made frequent and largescale use of the outlawed weapons against 
iranian forces 
velayati and ambassador mohammad jaafar mahallati of iran told 
reporters monday that iran wants the secretarygeneral to go ahead 
and name the ceasefire date with or without iraqs agreement 
iran is immediately ready to implement a un peace 
resolution by a ceasefire mahallati said 
perez de cuellar said it was theoretically correct he could 
unilaterally announce a ceasefire date but i prefer to wait for 
my team be in touch with members of the council and perhaps the 
parties 
he said he hoped for the shortest possible period between 
the announcement of a dday and the beginning of a ceasefire 
the war which began in september 1980 has cost an estimated 1 
million lives 
in response to questions the un chief said that if he or the 
council declared a ceasefire and one side does not respect it 
that is for the council to decide 
velayati told reporters all major issues have been covered in 
their meetings and there is no substantial point of 
disagreement between us and the secretarygeneral 
velayati also said we think that especially after recent use 
of chemical weapons now the security council should do 
something against iraq 
the experts detailed report mentioned nine iraqi soldiers 
poisoned in a battle zone allegedly in a mustard gas attack by 
iran 
other un reports have said iraq used chemical weapons which 
are outlawed under the 1925 geneva convention and the security 
council recently condemned use of the illegal weapons in the war 
sadoun hamadi iraqi minister of state for foreign affairs 
earlier monday repeated his countrys insistence on direct talks 
before a truce during an appearance on state television in baghdad 
the 15member security council gave unanimous approval july 20 
1987 to resolution 598 which provides for a ceasefire 
withdrawal to recognized borders prisoner exchange peace 
negotiations and an investigation to determine which side started 
the war in september 1980 
iraq agreed to accept the resolution soon after it was passed 
last summer but iran had refused until two weeks ago july 18 
the chemical weapons report was prepared by two specialist 
physicians who visited both countries in early july 
we deeply regret to say that on the basis of evidence gathered 
and in spite of repeated appeals by the united nations chemical 
weapons continue to be used on an intensive scale against iranian 
forces it said 
from the examination of weapon fragements it can be concluded 
that bombs similar to those used in 1984 1986 and 1987 have again 
been used against iranian forces on iranian territory indicating 
their repeated utilization by iraqi forces 
iraq has acknowledged using chemical weapons but claims iran 
introduced them to the war 
