joseph laitin a longtime government press officer who worked 
for shultz at the office and management and budget tried to 
explain shultz this way 
you have to remember the animal trainer describing how an 
elephant moves he puts one leg forward shifts his body over to 
that foot to see if it will hold him then moves the next foot 
forward he never leaves his moorings in one place without having 
another mooring hes no great risktaker 
the ringing declaration the apocalyptic pronouncement were not 
shultzs style he didnt convey the impression that the worlds 
fate hinged on his success in persuading foreign leaders to support 
his policies 
for six years plodding through ussoviet middle east arms 
control diplomacy he methodically recited to reporters you 
dont have an agreement until you have an agreement which seems 
to echo baseballs yogi berras it aint over till its over 
but if reporters found the secretary less than electrifying 
neither did he play games with them such as hiding behind 
background and notforattribution rituals in the ancient 
washington tradition he said what he had to say on the record 
even when it meant admitting the failure of a highstakes mission 
and he persevered he worked in behalf of jews and other 
minorities who were prevented from emigrating from the soviet 
union he made a point of giving human rights a pride of place 
on his agenda in all his sessions with soviet leaders he arranged 
meetings with dissidents in moscow and emigres in jerusalem to lend 
symbolic support to their cause 
lowkey team player that he was much of the time shultz could 
dissent sharply and publicly he bristled at a white house order in 
1985 to subject all government officials in sensitive positions to 
lie detector tests shultz would have none of it personally and 
threatened to resign unless the order was modified it was 
when reagan two years ago decided to sell subsidized wheat to 
the soviet union shultz called the sales ridiculous having 
led the opposition within the administration he kept up his 
criticism after he lost the soviets he said must be chortling 
over paying less for americanproduced food than american 
housewives 
there was risk in such selfassertion shultz told the house and 
senate irancontras investigating committees you must be willing 
to say goodbye and i am 
he had offered to quit on two other occasions 
one was in 1983 when he discovered that robert c mcfarlane 
then the deputy national security adviser had made a secret trip 
to several mideast states without shultzs knowledge he said he 
told reagan mr president you dont need a guy like me for 
secretary of state if this is the way things are going to be done 
the other came in august 1986 when shultz thought some 
conservatives in the white house subjected him to a kind of 
guerrilla warfare to the point of hamstringing his authority to 
use government aircraft for his state department business 
shultz served in the marines in world war ii and met his wife 
helena obrien in hawaii where she was an army nurse they have 
five children and five grandchildren 
when reagan asked shultz to succeed alexander haig jr in june 
1982 he was summoned from london where he had been on a business 
trip shultz was to meet with the president at camp david and he 
found two limousines waiting for him at the airport one was for 
him he was told the other to take his wife wherever she wanted to 
go while he had his interview with the president 
shultz waved off the second car no she will come with me 
he said we are a package deal 
he is the first man in history to have served in four cabinet 
posts state labor treasury and the office of management and 
budget 11 years in all of cabinet service a measure of his 
aptitude for conciliation and avoiding controversy is that he held 
three of these posts under richard m nixon and emerged unscathed 
by any of that administrations notoriety and scandal 
joseph laitins theory shared by others is that while shultz 
is a team player he also has a welldeveloped protective 
mechanism 
it was not that he was fighting them all the time says 
laitin there was an oldshoe relationship between shultz and 
nixon shultz will go along but at some point instinctively hell 
hunker down he will not budge because hes a man of character 
as secretary of the treasury he disregarded a nixon white house 
request to have the internal revenue service harass enemies of 
the administration provoking nixon to unflattering comments and 
when nixon complained about an irs audit of his tax return shultz 
told him that every recent president had been similarly audited 
he showed no signs of winding down as his tenure neared its end 
so far this year shultz has made four trips to the middle east 
three to the soviet union and a 17day swing through asia 
why did he keep returning to the mideast despite the refusal of 
israelis and arabs to heed his plea to negotiate shultz explained 
he didnt mind fighting long odds and if he didnt succeed 
himself he wanted to lay some groundwork for his successor 
besides he said what am i saving myself for 
end adv for sunday aug 14 
