<TEXT>
 
panther yauarete columbia milton nascimento 
 
milton nascimento has a unique ability to combine primitive 
folklike melodies with sophisticated jazzinspired harmonies the 
result is music of unusual depth and complexity with moods ranging 
from jubilant to mournful 
yauarete contains a diverse collection of nascimentos 
latest compositions it can be listened to either as a showcase of 
those compositions or as the evocative performance of one of 
brazils most moving singers 
on the one hand the freshness and originality of the 11 songs 
on the album attest to nascimentos seemingly inexhaustible 
creative energy and the breadth of his talent meu mestre coracao 
heart is my master a deftly engaging bossa nova follows a 
meditative excursion entitled cidade encantada enchanted city 
cancoes e moments songs and moments is a short repeating 
refrain that nascimento has recently used as a closing number 
during live performances leaving the audience quietly singing it 
as he and the band gradually drift offstage each song on the 
record is different and each reveals another facet of nascimentos 
compositional skill 
even if nascimento hadnt written the songs however this album 
would be remarkable merely for his performances his voice is rough 
but powerful and it is often tinged with a bittersweet longing 
with one exception the songs on yauarete are sung in 
portuguese but the feeling in nascimentos voice carries across 
the language barrier columbia has however printed english 
translations alongside the portuguese lyrics on the albums inner 
sleeve nascimento works closely with several lyricists who 
generally supply the words to go with his music 
</TEXT>
