<DOCNO> AP880801-0260 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
agb television research is suspending its us 
television ratings operation saying it underestimated the costs of 
competing with audience measurement leader ac nielsen 
the disclosure disappointed some advertising and television 
industry executives who said agb had provided some competition in 
the national tv ratings arena that has been dominated for 30 years 
by nielsen 
they had breathed some life into what had been an inactive 
portion of the business an executive of a major advertiser said 
monday speaking on condition he not be identified 
but others said nielsen still faces potential competition from 
companies such as arbitron ratings co which has announced plans 
to launch a national tv ratings service over the next few years 
that also will monitor buying habits 
agb a limited partnership in which the british concern agb 
research plc had a major interest is widely credited or blamed 
depending on the view with encouraging use of people meters 
in measuring national tv audiences 
the people meter is a handheld device that not only 
electronically records when the television is on but permits 
viewers to push buttons to record exactly who is watching at any 
given time 
after years of use in europe agb decided to employ the devices 
as it launched its us television ratings operation in the fall of 
1987 
nielsen had been testing its own people meter and announced it 
would rely on the device for its 198788 ratings as well under its 
old system nielsen used a combination of meters to measure when 
sets were on and handwritten diaries to tell who watched particular 
shows 
critics of the old system said an explosion in viewing choices 
made it increasingly unrealistic for anyone to record accurately in 
a diary what everyone in the family watched but others said the 
people meters have shortcomings as well such as in measuring 
viewing by children 
if it hadnt been for agb coming into the market with their 
people meter i dont think nielsen would have come out as soon 
with their people meter said jack otter a senior vice president 
at the advertising agency mccannerickson worldwide 
but the cost of the ratings service was more than agb had 
expected 
the londonbased agb research said it had estimated in april 
1987 that it would cost 49 million for the us service but that 
within a year the complexities of the market had driven costs past 
67 million 
following discussions with the tv networks advertising 
agencies and advertisers it became clear that despite considerable 
support the prospects for future revenue would not make the 
project viable and would be unlikely to cover the increased level 
of costs the company said 
this past spring agb approached the three major television 
networks in an effort to get all three to sign up for this fall and 
beyond 
cbs had been the only major network to subscribe to the agb 
ratings in the 198788 season and getting abc and nbc to join was 
seen not only as a way to boost revenue for agb but also as a 
signal to advertisers and their agencies of the prospects for the 
service 
it is disappointing to have one of the competitors gone 
said paul sonkin vice president for network audience research at 
capital citiesabc but he said abc decided against subscribing 
because of the cost 
asked for a response to agbs announcement nielsens chairman 
and chief executive john c holt said our operating assumption 
that the television audience measurement business is a competitive 
one remains unchanged 
at arbitron spokeswoman nan myers said the agb decision will 
have no effect on that companys plans which call for introduction 
of a system that monitors both viewing and buying habits in five 
major markets in the fall of 1989 and expansion into a national 
system in the fall of 1990 
she noted arbitron has been measuring local audiences in the 
united states for years and has a longterm commitment to a 
national service 
in announcing arbtrons plans in june arbitron presdident aj 
aurichio said he expected arbitron would lose 125 million on the 
syswtem over four to five years before breaking even in 1995 
in announcing the suspension of its television ratings service 
agb research also announced it would acquire mediamark research 
inc which measures magazine audiences in an exchange of stock 
timothy joyce chairman of mediamark said agbs choice of the 
word suspension in describing the status of its agb television 
operation in the united states was deliberate leaving open the 
possibility that it could be resurrected in another form at some 
future date 
</TEXT>
